                    <span>Read this and vote accordingly! The links between big business in the USA and between the House of Saud are truly scary. Granted, the Crown Prince really does want to reform the country, and should be credited accordingly, but many of the House of Saud are not so inclined and if Saudi Arabia blows up it will make Iran in 1979 look like a picnic in comparison. We should urgently be working towards empowering the small core of pro-Western Saudis rather than making deals with the Princes, and this book shows us how in a very thorough way. Christopher Catherwood, author of CHURCHILL'S FOLLY: HOW WINSTON CHURCHILL CREATED IRAQ (Carroll and Graf 2004)</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Must read for the informed voter</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
